'''Eskalera Karakola''' is a [[squatting|squat]] in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], which is held by [[feminist]]s and works on [[autogestion]] principles. It was situated in the [[Lavapiés]] barrio from 1996 to 2005,<ref>{{cite news|title=Las integrantes del centro Eskalera Karakola serán desalojadas mañana|url=http://elpais.com/diario/2005/05/09/madrid/1115637867_850215.html|newspaper=El País|date=9 May 2005}}</ref> and is now in Calle Embajador. The squat organizes activities focussing on [[domestic violence]] and women's [[precarity]] in [[post-industrial capitalism]].<ref>{{cite news|title=La Eskalera Karakola: Un espacio deliberado|url=http://www.sindominio.net/karakola/antigua_casa/textos/articulomolo.htm|newspaper=El Molotov|date=March 2003}}</ref> In 2002, it created a ''Female Workers' Laboratory'' (''Laboratorio de Trabajadoras''), and has carried out [[anti-racist]] activities, in particular with female [[Immigration to Spain|immigrants]], since 1998. Eskalera Karakola also took part in the organization of the [[Gay Pride|GLBT Pride]] and the forum "Women and Architecture". It participated in [[alter-globalization]] events such as the [[European Social Forum]] and is part of the European [http://www.nextgenderation.net/ nextGENDERation network]. It publishes a review, ''Mujeres Preokupando'' ("Concerned Women").<ref>{{cite book|first=Javier Alcalde |last=Villacampa |first2= Ramón Adell |last2=Argilés |first3= Miguel Martínez |last3= López|title=¿ Dónde están las llaves? El movimiento okupa: Prácticas y contextos sociales|year=2004|publisher=Los Libros de la Catarata|location=Madrid|isbn=9788483191828|pages=220-226|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=4cEozFIcYssC&lpg=PA220&ots=ZLbWk4W7xo&dq=Eskalera%20Karakola%20Mujeres%20Preokupando&pg=PA220#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>
